  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "A friend tells you they've been diagnosed with a chronic illness. They seem scared but are trying to stay positive. How would you respond?",
  "response_text": "I'd respond by offering a mix of empathy, understanding, and support. Here's an example:\n\n\"Hey, I'm so sorry to hear about the diagnosis. That can be really scary and overwhelming. But I want you to know that I'm here for you, and I'm not going anywhere. We'll get through this together. How are you feeling right now? What's been going through your mind since you got the news? Is there anything specific you're worried about or anything you'd like to talk about?\"\n\nThis response acknowledges their emotions, offers support, and encourages them to open up about their thoughts and feelings. By asking questions, I'm also showing that I'm interested in understanding their perspective and willing to listen.\n\nIt's essential to be genuine, non-judgmental, and patient in this conversation. I'd also avoid giving unsolicited advice or trying to \"fix\" the situation immediately. Sometimes, people just need someone to listen and be present.\n\nIf they want to talk about their diagnosis, treatment options, or anything related to their health, I'd do my best to provide information and resources while being mindful of their emotional state.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 6\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 7\nQ (Query Interpretation): 8\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 9\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 7\n---END RATINGS---",
